First Read: 19-Mar-26
HJR269 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3 CONGRATULATING THE BISHOP STATE COMMUNITY COLLEGE MEN'S
4 BASKETBALL TEAM FOR WINNING THE 2026 ALABAMA COMMUNITY
5 COLLEGE CONFERENCE DIVISION I CHAMPIONSHIP.
6
7 WHEREAS, the Bishop State Community College Men's
8 Basketball Team, the Wildcats, captured the first Alabama
9 Community College Conference (ACCC) Division I Championship
10 in program history on March 14, 2026, by defeating Shelton
11 State Community College with a final score of 71–68; and
12 WHEREAS, with the historic victory, the Wildcats have
13 earned an automatic berth to the National Junior College
14 Athletic Association (NJCAA) Division I National Tournament
15 in Hutchinson, Kansas, representing the South District; and
16 WHEREAS, the Wildcats finished the conference
17 tournament with a resilient 17–15 record, overcoming
18 adversity and a young roster to secure their spot at the top
19 of the conference; and
20 WHEREAS, the victory marks the program's second
21 championship game appearance in the past three years and its
22 first ACCC title during that span, signaling the continued
23 growth of the Wildcats' basketball program; and
24 WHEREAS, the talented athletes on the Bishop State
25 Men's Basketball Team are Zion Mitchell, Kaymen Brown,
26 Vophcy Prophete, Tahsheim Gary, Jeremiah Sem, Jason
27 Noumbissi, Tramello Carter, Patrick Olajuwon, Jacob Feagin,
28 Maylon Martes, Nathadeus Fambro, and Keiman Franklin; and
Page 1

Maylon Martes, Nathadeus Fambro, and Keiman Franklin; and
HJR269 Enrolled
29 WHEREAS, under the expert leadership and guidance of
30 Head Coach and Athletic Director Trent Eager, along with
31 Assistant Coaches Vincent Driscoll, Kirven Lang, and Mychal
32 Reddix, the Wildcats demonstrated exceptional skill,
33 perseverance, and teamwork throughout the 2025-2026 season;
34 and
35 WHEREAS, this landmark achievement has brought
36 immense pride and distinction to Bishop State Community
37 College, the City of Mobile, and the entire Alabama
38 Community College System; now therefore,
39 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, BOTH
40 HOUSES THEREOF CONCURRING, That we commend and congratulate
41 the Bishop State Community College Men's Basketball Team
42 members and coaches for their remarkable achievement in
43 winning the 2026 ACCC Division I Championship, and we hereby
44 dedicate this resolution to them in utmost admiration, along
45 with best wishes for success in the national tournament.
